<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFGisela_Procházka-EislStephan_Procházka2010" class="citation book cs1">Gisela Procházka-Eisl; Stephan Procházka (2010). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Ixl3NcvAixAC&amp;pg=PA20"><i>The Plain of Saints and Prophets: The Nusayri-Alawi Community of Cilicia (Southern Turkey) and Its Sacred Places</i></a>. Otto Harrassowitz Verlag. p.&#160;20. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-3-447-06178-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-3-447-06178-0"><bdi>978-3-447-06178-0</bdi></a>. <q>...for nearly a millennium the term by far most often used in both Oriental and Western sources for this group has been 'Nusayri'.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Plain+of+Saints+and+Prophets%3A+The+Nusayri-Alawi+Community+of+Cilicia+%28Southern+Turkey%29+and+Its+Sacred+Places&amp;rft.pages=20&amp;rft.pub=Otto+Harrassowitz+Verlag&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=978-3-447-06178-0&amp;rft.au=Gisela+Proch%C3%A1zka-Eisl&amp;rft.au=Stephan+Proch%C3%A1zka&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DIxl3NcvAixAC%26pg%3DPA20&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAlawites" class="Z3988"></span></span>
